<doc id="1122674" wikidata="Q171782" url="?curid=1122674" title="1976 Dutch Grand Prix">
<text>The 1976 Dutch Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race held at Circuit Zandvoort on 29 August 1976. It was won by British driver James Hunt driving a McLaren M23 on his 29th birthday. The race, contested over 75 laps, was the twelfth round of the 1976 Formula One season.

The weekend was marred by the death of track marshal Ron Lenderink during a touring car support race. He was 29.

== Qualifying ==

=== Qualifying classification ===
== Race ==

=== Race classification ===
==Notes==

* This was the Formula One World Championship debut for Swedish driver Conny Andersson and Dutch driver Bob Hayje.
* This race marked the 100th podium finish for an American driver.
* This was the 10th Grand Prix start for Wolf-Williams.
* This race saw the 5th pole position for a March.

